IEADB treats Serbia as having assumed the IEADB commitments of Yugoslavia and of Serbia and Montenegro. Therefore, while modern-day Serbia officially formed on 20060605 (but reported as 20060603 for IMO treaties and some others), it is treated as having formed on 19431129, the date Yugoslavia was formed, to capture continuous membership from the period of the original Yugoslavia.
